<Author>citrob
<Content>Wonderful place This was a wonderful place to stay! The rooms were very clean, with service and new towels everyday. Others thought the rooms were on the small side, particularly the less expensive rooms, but ours was bigger than expected. Sure, it's smaller than a typical room in the U.S., but for the value, we had a nice bathroom with a full tub and plenty of room for our things. There is a nice courtyard, which makes for quite evenings being off the street. Also, location is awesome: very close to Notre Dame, Pantheon, late-night cafes and bars, and metro. Front desk folks were very nice on arrival and departure. We didn't have breakfast as there are plenty of places around to grab something to eat. However, we saw plenty of other folks enjoying themselves in the morning. We would most definately recommend staying here and look forward to returning soon! 
