<Author>FrequentFlyer28
<Content>First time to Paris This charming hotel is tucked away behind tall gates on the Rue de Cardinal Lemoine. A small sign is the only thing indicating its presence. Upon opening the gates, one finds oneself in a lovely garden courtyard. Very welcoming.While our command of the French language certainly improved during our stay in Paris, we were initially hesitant and unsure of our communication skills. The hotel staff were most gracious and helpful in this regard. They encouraged our attempts at French, but were also very capable of helping us in English. We soon found ourselves in a delightful, third floor room with a beautiful view of the courtyard below.The rooms are small, of course, and very clean. The beds comfortable. There are no televisions, no radios. It was explained to us that this is because the hotel is very old, and the noise would be potentially disturbing to other guests. The bathrooms are clean. Some have tubs but most are shower equipped. Toilet paper was sometimes insufficient and you might want to bring your own Kleenex as it seems to be scarce in Paris. Location is good. Latin Quarter is charming and bohemian. Walking in the neighbourhood is a pleasure. Metro close by. Patisseries on many corners. Incomparable pastries. They truly are works of art!! 
