<Author>redheadjeanne
<Content>Friendly, Lovely and Affordable I've stayed at Hotel des Grandes Ecoles about 5 times and each time has been a gem. The rooms are pleasant and the staff very helpful. The garden is welcoming and the breakfast room very sweet.This is a family - run business and not backed by any sort of corporate entity, so there are some rough spots, none of which would ever keep me from returning. Some folks have had trouble with reservations, but I never have. When I am certain i am coming and have specific dates, I follow their website suggestions to the tee. I send an email as early on the 15th of the month 4 months ahead requesting my dates. They send an email back confirming availability and requesting a credit card. They don't actually use the credit card unless you're a no-show. I've also sent an email when my dates are more flexible and I've missed the deadline -- do you have 4 consecutive nights in June? And I've had some success with that.The reservation complaints have subsided, I think, and they may have been caused by the transition from their old pencil and paper system (that defied all understanding) to a computer-based system.Can't recommend this place highly enough. Just warm and fun and well located. But it doesn't have the amenities of a chain hotel (which is what I like about it ... I bring my own soap and shampoo).p.s. While a lot of guide books suggest eating breakfast at a cafe to save $$, we love the 9 E breakfast. 
