<Content>A Wee Gem highly recommended-great hotel in great location- book it now!!!i stayed in this hotel based on recommendations from TripAdviser posts.. a great little hotel hidden away from the hustle and bustle of Paris.. it's not too glam or salubrious but if you just want somewhere to retire to after a days sight seeing this is the place to go. it's clean and great value for money.we had very little interaction with the staff so i can't comment on them but htey seemed friendly enough (during our weekend in paris i never encountered any of the infamous rudeness- i must say i was a little disappointed)we didn't eat there, there's a square around the corner from the hotel and we had our breakfasts there instead, a bit pricey but you go to paris for value and what better way to enjoy a morning coffee than sitting on the terrace watching paris waking up for another day of chicness???The only things that may put a body off staying are that the rooms are basic and small, the floral print wallpaper is not to be looked at when hungover (and they have covered every surface in the room with it) there's no TV or any of that modern nonsense but when you've the city of lights as a backdrop who needs the telly??? None of these bothered us in fact they added to the charm of the place and i'd deffinelty try and book it again the next time i'm in paris but judging by its popularity on TAdvisor i'll probably have to book a year in advance.... i found some grat bars and restaurants in the area too if you want to message me about them 
