<Content>Quiet, clean, convenient, and friendly We booked three nights at this hotel through the web, and had no problems with the reservation at all. The location is very convenient to the Metro (1 block up from the Cardinal Lemoine station), easily reached from the train station (we came on the high-speed Thalys train from Belgium) and yet the hotel is amazingly quiet. It's set back from the Rue Cardinal Lemoine by a tall gated wall, and has a lovely courtyard garden. Your room key opens the outside gate for coming back to your room after 10:00 pm.We had a quad room, with our two teenage children staying with us. The price for this 4-person room was very fair at 150 Euro per night, which was slightly lower than quotes at other lower-rated hotels in the Latin Quarter. Our room was on the third floor, in a corner of the building facing away from the street, and had large windows opening onto both the garden and the entrance walkway, plus a private bathroom with shower. The two beds consisted of a queen size bed and a pull-out double bed from a couch, but they were suitably comfortable. The room also included a small table and chairs, plus adequate closet space. It was very clean and well maintained, and the bathroom was spotless with plenty of linens and soaps. Although it was not air conditioned, there were two fans in the room, which we didn't need due to an unusually cool week in August (low 60s at night).The staff were very friendly and helpful, and were quite patient with my destruction of the French language. We did not take the hotel breakfast, but instead opted for croissants from patisseries along the way at much lower cost. We were also able to store our bags in the lobby/office after checkout for several hours until our train departure.The location is simply wonderful, less than a 10-minute walk to Notre Dame, two blocks from many restaurants and shops on the Rue Mouffetard, and two blocks from the Pantheon. There are plenty of small cafes and brasseries nearby, along with a small supermarket, ATM, and creperies for snacks or lunch. I would highly recommend this hotel to anyone who is seeking a clean, comfortable, and quiet place to stay in the left bank. We will absolutely stay here again on our next trip to Paris. 
