<Content>Our Second Stay to Celebrate Our 20th Wedding Anniversary in Paris. Our first stay was in 2003 when I booked this hotel from their website on the internet based on the website. We couldn't have been more pleased. From the location near the Pantheon and the Sorbonne on the Left Bank to the private entrance through a gate on the street and up a cobblestone walkway to the separate buildings surrounding the cobblestone courtyard, it was ideal. The distance from the street provides a quiet, restful stay. The hotel is run by Madame, the proprietor and under the direction of Marie Le Floch who provide warm and personal service. The staff are all courteous and friendly. We espcially liked the decor of the rooms which is very homey and gives an ambiance of a quaint hotel rather than a large, chain facility. The breakfast room off the office in the main building is similar and very comfortable. The continental breakfast includes the wonderful baked goods of Paris. The rooms are without TV also which adds to the restful, quiet atmosphere like the location away from the street provides a quiet outdoor atmosphere. The courtyard provides a gathering place for guests for breakfast if perferred to the indoor breakfast room or room service in your room. It also is a gathering place espcially in the evening for people to enjoy food and drink they purchase elsewhere or from the hotel. The location is near a Metro station and just uphill on the Rue Cardinal Lemoine is the Place Contrescarpe with cafes and eateries. Down the opposite side of the hill from the hotel is well-known Rue Mouffetard which is lined on both sides with eateries, cafes, shops, an ATM and a market at the bottom of the Rue. And so my wife and I booked as early as possible on the hotel website and enjoyed our second stay as much or more than the last. We will always plan to stay there when we are visiting Paris. We were able this time to stay for ten days and we are already missing Paris and the hotel. Feel free to contact us if you have any questions about our stay. 
